{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2521", "repo": "rails", "body": "So the naming is already inconsistant with the implementation, and this change will make the validator do what users would expect when it's applied to a boolean. As a relatively recent convert to rails, I've been continuously told of how rails is all about sensible defaults and supporting DRY-ing up your code. This patch supports both of these principles.\r\n\r\nI'm not going to get into a flame war, this will be my last post on the issue.", "_id": {"$oid": "523842c5bd3543c151010b60"}, "issue_id": 2521, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1802136", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2521#issuecomment-1802136", "updated_at": "2011-08-14T16:26:40Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon", "login": "BrentWheeldon", "gravatar_id": "04e37f7d55bdb2b2871834700fa30c97", "html_url": "https://github.com/BrentWheeldon", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/04e37f7d55bdb2b2871834700fa30c97?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F7b8209725ca54c612810263e9dfea47d.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 764206, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BrentWheeldon/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-08-14T16:26:40Z", "id": 1802136, "owner": "rails"}
